==English==

===Etymology===
[[Back-formation]] from the Latin name of the [[order]], '''[[Primates]]''', the plural of '''[[primas]]''', ''one of the first, excellent, noble''

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# Any mammal of the [[order]] ''Primates'', including the lemurs, monkeys, apes and humans.
# {{theology}} In the [[Western Church]], an [[archbishop]] or [[bishop]] who has authority over a number of provinces.<!--this sense probably has a different etymology-->

